.SH NAME
KeyboardEvent.ctrlKey \- KeyboardEvent: ctrlKey property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]KeyboardEvent.ctrlKey\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns a boolean value that indicates if the control key was pressed
(\f[CR]true\f[R]) or not (\f[CR]false\f[R]) when the event occurred.
.SH VALUE
A boolean value.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
